Source: libfile-locate-iterator-perl
Section: perl
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 5), libtest-more-perl | perl-modules (>= 5.6.2)
Maintainer: Kevin Ryde <user42@zip.com.au>
Standards-Version: 3.8.3
Homepage: http://user42.tuxfamily.org/file-locate-iterator/index.html
Bugs: mailto:user42@zip.com.au

Package: libfile-locate-iterator-perl
Architecture: all
Depends: perl (>= 5.6), libfile-fnmatch-perl, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: libiterator-perl, libiterator-simple-perl
Description: Read a "locate" database file with an iterator
 File::Locate::Iterator reads a "locate" database file, similar to
 File::Locate, but done as an iterator rather than callbacks.
 .
 Optional support for Iterator or Iterator::Simple iterators is
 included, or the module can be used stand-alone.
